            "description": "I organized the company visit for more than one hundred 4th graders from Beanstalk International Bilingual School (BIBS).\n\nGoldwind is committing itself to a better future for mankind through the development of clean energy and facilitating solutions to solve social and environmental problems. The goal was to provide the students of Beanstalk an understanding of green energy and advocate for the conversation of energy and the protection of the environment. During the company visit, the students received a presentation on global climate change and the development of green energy, got the opportunity to see our greenhouse where we produce vegetables with the energy from wind and solar, the micro-grid system to storage energy, the inside of a wind turbine nacelle and hub. Overall the company visit was more than successful and has become a part of the student learnings field trips.\n",
